news.title: Mysuru development body allegedly allocates 1,095 sites worth Rs 700 crore in Benami land deals
news.para: Lokayukta sources confirmed they'd received such an information from ED. Both agencies are probing the Muda alternative site allotment scam in which chief minister Siddaramaiah and his wife are among the accused.

news.title: Hubballi-Dharwad civic body to install 75,000 LED streetlights
news.para: The corporation has begun the process to install 75,000 LED streetlights, with an investment of Rs 94 crore through a public-private partnership model.

news.title: Gujarat: Proposed jantri rates could make GIDC plots and private industrial land costlier
news.para: Officials in the state industries department have pointed out that the timing of land acquisition for new GIDC estates now becomes crucial.

news.title: Kumaon commissioner cracks down on illegal construction and land encroachments in Nainital
news.para: The inspection revealed that over 15 parks in various phases of the project were illegally sold, after which, an order halting all transactions involving these lands was issued.

news.title: Karnataka: Homestay owners of Chikkamagaluru seek non-commercial status for properties
news.para: The association claimed the authorities were known to impose high taxes, and the land where homestays were established was required to be converted into commercial land.

news.title: Lucknow development body mandates rooftop solar panels for 1,000 sq ft plots
news.para: During its 183rd board meeting held on Wednesday, the LDA made it mandatory for all residential properties with a plot size of 1,000 square feet or more to install rooftop solar panels under the PM Surya Ghar scheme.

news.title: Kochi civic body faces allegations of bribery and building violations
news.para: A revenue officer was suspended and a probe ordered into five different cases of alleged building rule violations and charges of bribery on Wednesday.

news.title: Need to make land available to provide habitation for people: Housing secretary
news.para: Addressing a CII conference on Affordable Housing, he emphasised on the need to move away from housing to habitation as well as from owned assets to sharing and rentals.

news.title: Suraj Estate Developers' subsidiary acquires 15,758 sq ft land in Mumbai for Rs 101 crore
news.para: Suraj Estate Developers plans to develop a commercial building with an estimated carpet area of 1.03 lakh sq ft with a gross development value (GDV) of around Rs 525 crore.

news.title: Smart villages should be built on the line of smart cities: Nitin Gadkari
news.para: "So that thing is in my mind. I am also making a smart village. A plot of 1,000 square feet, a house of 500 square feet in Rs 5 lakh... and for entire life the electricity and water are free," the minister said.

news.title: Microsoft India buys land parcel for Rs 181.25 crore from Natco Pharma in Hyderabad
news.para: The 121,000 square yard plot is located in the Nandigama village in Telangana, according to a sales deed shared by Propstack.

news.title: Gurugram: Three posing as Orris Infrastructure agents cheat buyers of Rs 1 crore
news.para: This came to light after Puneet Sain, the company's representative, registered a cheating case against Gurmet Singh, Parminder from Palam Vihar, and others involved in the scam.

news.title: SC directs Karnataka govt to pay current market value for land acquired in 1986
news.para: The bench said, "The award of Apr 21, 1986, does not absolve the Karnataka government of paying fair and just compensation. Denial of paying compensation is violative of Article 300A (right to property).

news.title: Star Cement promoters deny stake sale talks with Adani Group
news.para: Star Cement currently operates an integrated cement plant in Meghalaya and two grinding units in Guwahati (4 million tonnes) and Siliguri, West Bengal (2 million tonnes).

news.title: Builders must adhere to quake-resistant norms for occupancy certificate: Experts
news.para: "There are separate norms for buildings, water tanks, and even important structures like dams," said Virendra Dehadrai, a structural engineer.

news.title: PropShare Platina IPO subscribed 1.2 times on last day
news.para: The issue received bids of 4,002 units against the offered 3,353 units, according to data available on the stock exchange.

news.title: Buyers struggle as Karnataka apartment ownership act enactment gets delayed
news.para: The proposed new Act is expected to benefit homebuyers who are facing problems in forming associations and getting the rights on common areas transferred from promoters to flat owners’ associations.

news.title: Gurugram DC warns builders over safety audit delays
news.para: Deputy commissioner Ajay Kumar expressed dissatisfaction with builders delaying deposit of their share of audit fees, calling such behaviour ‘irresponsible' towards citizens' safety.

news.title: SC grants bail to SRS group's chairperson in Rs 770 crore fraud case
news.para: A bench comprising Chief Justice Sanjiv Khanna and Justice Sanjay Kumar observed that Jindal had been in jail for the last six-and-half years and the trial in the case was yet to begin.

news.title: Norway government eases loan-to-value mortgage limit to 90%
news.para: The revised rule set a maximum loan-to-value mortgage ratio of 90%, up from 85% previously, requiring borrowers to put up 10% equity when buying a home, down from 15% previously.
